    {
      "id": "PopularPost316930",
      "post_content": "The regular casting cost is far too high, but it has a decent flashback cost. At least in a mono-colored deck (even though they could have easily made the cost ![3](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=3&type=symbol)![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol)![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol)![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol) instead). Oh well, one red mana for each mayor boulder it is.  \nStill, it doesn't seem to make sense than that you only need ONE red mana for the regular casting cost. Also, ![3](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=3&type=symbol)![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol)![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol)![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol)![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol)![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol)![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol) would have been a great thing with *Chroma*.  \n  \nBut even with a cost of ![8](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=8&type=symbol)![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol), you can still try to turn that into an advantage.  \nJust make sure to pack your deck with discard effects that look at the CMC.  \nYou'll deal a lot of damage discarding it, and will be able to cast it from your graveyard next turn:  \n  \n- [Blast of Genius](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Blast of Genius): Draw three cards, discard VoB and deal 9 damage.  \n- [Mercurial Chemister](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mercurial Chemister): His second ability gets even more ridiculous if you have multiple VoB's in hand.  \n- [Kindle the Carnage](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Kindle the Carnage): If there's only this and VoB in hand, 4.5 [Pyroclasm](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Pyroclasm)s should pre... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Mode",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost316930\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_post\">The regular casting cost is far too high, but it has a decent flashback cost. At least in a mono-colored deck (even though they could have easily made the cost <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"3\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=3&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Red\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=R&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Red\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=R&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Red\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=R&amp;type=symbol\"/> instead). Oh well, one red mana for each mayor boulder it is.<br/>Still, it doesn't seem to make sense than that you only need ONE red mana for the regular casting cost. Also, <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"3\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=3&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Red\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=R&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Red\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=R&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Red\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=R&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Red\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=R&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Red\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=R&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Red\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=R&amp;type=symbol\"/> would have been a great thing with <i>Chroma</i>.<br/><br/>But even with a cost of <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"8\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=8&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Red\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=R&amp;type=symbol\"/>, you can still try to turn that into an advantage.<br/>Just make sure to pack your deck with discard effects that look at the CMC.<br/>You'll deal a lot of damage discarding it, and will be able to cast it from your graveyard next turn:<br/><br/>- <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Blast of Genius\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Blast of Genius\">Blast of Genius</a>: Draw three cards, discard VoB and deal 9 damage.<br/>- <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Mercurial Chemister\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mercurial Chemister\">Mercurial Chemister</a>: His second ability gets even more ridiculous if you have multiple VoB's in hand.<br/>- <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Kindle the Carnage\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Kindle the Carnage\">Kindle the Carnage</a>: If there's only this and VoB in hand, 4.5 <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Pyroclasm\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Pyroclasm\">Pyroclasm</a>s should pre... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 316930)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '316930'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy416\">Mode</span>\r\n                                (5/20/2013 1:18:00 AM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                               